      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right that the human cost doesn't always balance out neatly in simple calculations, especially when deep community changes are at stake. While those who lose from higher prices may thrive in value-added sectors, the broader consensus is that these industries cannot compete, leading to inefficient resource allocation and potential long-term stagnation. Rather than viewing this solely through a narrow economic lens, a comprehensive approach considers how these trade-offs might necessitate targeted social safety nets to support the displaced workers instead.",
      "source": "target",
